^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 301 - June 17, 2002^*N
^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
The Nickell Team (^*BNick Nickell^*N-^*BRichard Freeman^*N, ^*BJeff Meckstroth^*N-^*BEric Rodwell^*N, and ^*BBob Hamman^*N-^*BPaul Soloway^*N) has qualified to represent the United States in the 2003 Bermuda Bowl World Championships. Nickell defeated Schwartz (^*BRichard Schwartz^*N-^*BMike Becker^*N, ^*BDavid Berkowitz^*N-^*BLarry Cohen^*N, and ^*BZia Mahmood^*N-^*BMichael Rosenberg^*N) 261-232 in the 120-board final match at the ^*BUnited States Bridge Championships^*N in Memphis last week.

Every deal of the semi-finals and finals of this event was broadcast live through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N and I am very pleased to report that this broadcast was an unqualified success. Hundreds of players, including ^*Bmany^*N of the games brightest stars, were in the audience at all times. A number of these players (including ^*BMark Feldman^*N, ^*BMarty Fleischer^*N, ^*BAllan Graves^*N, ^*BAllen Kahn^*N, ^*BJustin Lall^*N, ^*BJan^*N and ^*BChip Martel^*N, ^*BBrad Moss^*N, ^*BShawn Quinn^*N, ^*BSteve Robinson^*N, ^*BTommy Sanders^*N, ^*BDoug Simson^*N, ^*BAdam Wildavsky^*N, and ^*BChris Willenken^*N - sorry if I left anyone out) provided excellent live commentary and analysis. ^*BDebbie Rosenberg^*N deserves special mention as she was a commentator for every session and we received a lot of e-mail feedback that praised the quality of Debbie's analysis and how well she was able to express herself.

The ^*BUnited States Bridge Federation^*N (in particular ^*BMichael Becker^*N and ^*BShawn Quinn^*N) deserve our thanks for making this broadcast possible. The ^*BAmerican Contract Bridge League^*N also contributed to the success of the show in a very big way. ACBL employees (Jim, Paul, Dave, and Butch) worked long and hard hours doing the data entry and ACBL management (notably ^*BGary Blaiss^*N and ^*BPeter Mollemet^*N) were instrumental in helping with logistic organization.

