There were a lot of fascinating deals in the 2002 United States Bridge Championships and the next several ^*BDeals of the Week^*N will feature some of my favorite deals from this tournament. This week's deal resulted in a lot of discussion among the vugraph commentators and audience. ^*BJeff Meckstroth^*N declared 3NT brilliantly on this deal and made his contract, but there was a lot of speculation that the defense could have done better.

In an effort to keep the show moving, I asked the various commentators to put this deal to rest and promised that I would fully analyze what could have happened in this week's ^*BDeal of the Week^*N. So here it is...

Each ^*BDeal of the Week^*N is normally posted either late Sunday night or early Monday morning. I am sorry that this week's deal (which was posted on a Tuesday) is late, but the pressures of playing in the United States Bridge Championships (my team lost to the Schwartz team in the semi-finals) and providing commentary for our live broadcast made it impossible for me to get this week's deal ready on schedule.



